So what you're saying is that, if someone in Europe were to download
a copy of nCrypt, the US government would try to get the *author* of
the program sent to prison???  The federal government never ceases to
amaze me.  It would seem that, if warnings were in place, that the
downloader would be the "guilty" party for having transported the
program outside the US.

